title: I Who Have Never Known Men
creator: Jaqueline Harpman
description: A young woman who grew up in a cage with 39 other women, guarded by faceless and silent men, by chance is given the opportunity to escape when an alarm causes the guards to flee. Her and the rest of the women venture out into the barren world above, trying to find meaning, friendship, freedom, and others who may be out there. Tessa's rating: 10/10
subject: science fiction; post-apocalyptic; dystopian

title: Drive Your Plow over the Bones of the Dead
creator: Olga Tokarczuk
description: A reclusive woman with a fondness for animals living in a Polish borderland village spends time studying the poetry of William Blake and astrology, when her neighbor turns up dead. An investigation begins, but the police don't seem to take her seriously... Tessa's rating: 6.5/10
subject: crime; mystery
image_alt_text: Olga in a large grey chair reading a book out loud

title: The Wall
creator: Marlen Haushofer
description: A middle aged woman wakes up one day surrounded by a (metaphorical) wall, where she seems to be the only person left on either side. She is kept company by her dog, cat, and cow as she writes an account of her daily isolation. Tessa's rating: 7/10
subject: science fiction; stream of consciousness; dystopian
image_alt_text: Black typewriter with white keys with a piece of paper inserted in. A book by Marlen Haushofer lays over the keys.

title: G
creator: John Berger
description: A young man named G. is a lover of women (although hated by many) operating in pre-World War I Europe. It is an interpretation of the Don Juan story. Tessa's rating: 1/10
subject: experimental; historical fiction
image_alt_text: Old man with white hair smiling in a striped blue and white shirt

title: The Idiot
creator: Fyodor Dostoyesvsky
description: Myshkin, a young prince with an open hearted simplicity (and various ailments), travels throughout Russia discussing life, society, love, religion, and intelligence while swapping stories at parties with family, generals, and beautiful women. Stay tuned for an exciting wedding scene. Tessa's rating: 7/10
subject: classic lit
image_alt_text: Part of a manuscript with a sketch of a man's head in the center with written text surrounding it

title: Fledgling
creator: Octavia Butler
description: Shori, a young Ina, wakes up alone in a cave, bruised and with no memories. She discovers her power and desires as she travels to find other communities of Ina, learning about where she came from and forging new ways of human/Ina symbiosis.
subject: science fiction; vampires; coming of age
image_alt_text: An older women with glasses signing a book

title: The Nickel Boys
creator: Colson Whitehead
description: Elmwood, a Black young man, was sent to a corrupt juvenile reform school in the 1960s, exposing the hidden atrocities and abuses of these academies.
subject: historical fiction; coming of age
image_alt_text: A man in a brown suit on a panel, speaking into a microphone

title: Moby Dick
creator: Herman Melville
description: Ishmael is looking for adventure and sets out on the Pequod with a mysterious and monomanical captian. He catalouges the oceanic world and the processes of whaling as the boat sails across the Atlantic, meeting others along the way.
subject: classic lit
image_alt_text: A manuscript first page of The Whale

title: Agua Viva
creator: Clarice Lispector
description: A stream of (life) consciousness filled with unconventional thoughts (about placentas, bats in caves, etc.) and emotions.
subject: experimental; stream of consciousness
image_alt_text: Black and white photo of a woman sitting in a chair looking straight onto the camera

title: Hard Rain Falling
creator: Don Carpenter
description: Life is a prison, except in actual prison. Set in the Pacific West Coast in the 1950s, Jack, our passive protagonist, lives his poor life in the outskirts of society; growing up in an orphanage, hanging out with the misfits on the corner, frequenting underground poolhalls, then becoming a prisioner, and an ex convist. He struggles with finding meaning in life, his relationships, dealing with society and its unjustness, and understanding his sexuality and who he is. Tessa's rating: 5/10 (well written but depressing)
subject: crime; historical fiction
image_alt_text: Sepia photograph of a man with galses and a salt and pepper beard

title: We Have Always Lived in the Castle
creator: Shirley Jackson
description: Two sisters and their wheelchair bound uncle are all that remain of the presitgious, mysterious, isolated, and muderous (?) Blackwood family, until their Cousin Charles shows up, despite 'protections' put around the house.
subject: thriller; mystery
image_alt_text: Painting of a Victorian house with fairies surrounding it
